- Install `eslint-plugin-next` and `@typescript-eslint/parser` using npm or yarn.
- Use `next.config.ts` for TypeScript configuration in Next.js projects.
- Ensure `typescript` option is set to `{}` in `next.config.ts`.
- Update `.eslintrc.json` with the following key configurations:
  ```json
  {
    "parser": "@typescript-eslint/parser",
    "plugins": ["@typescript-eslint", "next"],
    "extends": [
      "eslint:recommended",
      "plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended",
      "plugin:next/recommended"
    ],
    "rules": {
      // Custom rules here
    }
  }
  ```
- Run `npm run lint` or `yarn lint` to check for ESLint errors.
- Ensure TypeScript is enabled in your project by adding `"compilerOptions": { "target": "es5", "lib": ["dom", "es2015"], "jsx": "preserve" }` to `tsconfig.json`.

- Install Next.js and TypeScript: `npx create-next-app@latest --typescript`
- Add ESLint to your project: `npm install eslint @typescript-eslint/parser @typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin eslint-config-prettier eslint-plugin-prettier --save-dev`
- Initialize ESLint configuration: `npx eslint --init`
  - Choose "To check syntax, find problems, and enforce code style"
  - Select "JavaScript modules (import/export)"
  - Select "TypeScript"
  - Select "Browser" environment
  - Select "ESLint with Prettier"
- Update `.eslintrc.json`:
```json
{
  "parser": "@typescript-eslint/parser",
  "plugins": ["@typescript-eslint", "prettier"],
  "extends": [
    "eslint:recommended",
    "plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended",
    "plugin:prettier/recommended"
  ],
  "rules": {
    "prettier/prettier": "error"
  }
}
```
- Install Prettier: `npm install prettier --save-dev`
- Add Prettier configuration to `.prettierrc`:
```json
{
  "semi": true,
  "singleQuote": true,
  "trailingComma": "all"
}
```
- Run ESLint on your project: `npx eslint . --fix`
- Configure VSCode for automatic linting and formatting:
  - Install ESLint and Prettier extensions
  - Add to settings.json:
```json
{
  "editor.codeActionsOnSave": {
    "source.fixAll.eslint": true,
    "source.fixAll.prettier": true
  },
  "eslint.validate": [
    "javascript",
    "javascriptreact",
    "typescript",
    "typescriptreact"
  ],
  "prettier.requireConfig": true
}
```
- Update `tsconfig.json` to include ESLint paths:
```json
{
  "include": ["next-env.d.ts", "**/*.ts", "**/*.tsx"],
  "exclude": ["node_modules"]
}
```
- Run ESLint on your project: `npx eslint . --fix`
- Configure Next.js to use ESLint during builds:
  - Add to `next.config.js`:
```js
module.exports = {
  webpack(config, { isServer }) {
    if (isServer) {
      config.module.rules.push({
        test: /\.tsx?$/,
        exclude: /node_modules/,
        loader: 'eslint-loader',
        options: {
          fix: true,
        },
      });
    }
    return config;
  },
};
```
- Run ESLint on your project: `npx eslint . --fix`
